    <description><![CDATA[Redis is the open source, in-memory data store used by millions of developers as a database, cache, streaming engine, and message broker.

### Core capabilities

- In-memory data structures: Well-known as a "data structure server", with support for strings, hashes, lists, sets, sorted sets, streams, and more.
- Programmability: Server-side scripting with Lua and server-side stored procedures with Redis Functions.
- Extensibility: A module API for building custom extensions to Redis in C, C++, and Rust.
- Persistence: Keeps the dataset in memory for fast access, but can also persist all writes to permanent storage to survive reboots and system failures.
- Clustering: Horizontal scalability with hash-based sharding, scaling to millions of nodes with automatic re-partitioning when growing the cluster.
- High availability: Replication with automatic failover for both standalone and clustered deployments.

### Disclaimer

You should use it for local development and follow Redis official guidance to deploy it on Linux for production environment. This project doesn't bear any responsibility for any losses caused by using it and is only for learning and exchange purposes.
]]></description>
    <summary>Redis is the open source, in-memory data store used by millions of developers as a database, cache, streaming engine, and message broker.</summary>
    <releaseNotes><![CDATA[[Releases](https://github.com/redis-windows/redis-windows/releases)

Update urgency: `HIGH`: There are critical bugs that may affect a subset of users.

### Bug fixes

- https://github.com/redis/redis/pull/15175, RediSearch/RediSearch#9262 Redis fails to start on AArch64
- https://github.com/redis/redis/pull/15163 `MULTI` queue memory incorrect memory accounting 
- https://github.com/redis/redis/pull/15115 Under-copy in the Lua debugger
- https://github.com/redis/redis/pull/15094 Cluster crash when `CLIENT KILL` unsubscribes `SSUBSCRIBE` client inside `EXEC`
- https://github.com/redis/redis/pull/14963 `XREADGROUP`: consumer replication inconsistency
- https://github.com/redis/redis/pull/14934 Client output buffer memory tracking not accounting for copy-avoided bulk string references
- https://github.com/redis/redis/pull/14970 Sentinel config injection via `SENTINEL SET`
- https://github.com/redis/redis/pull/14982 `SCAN` commands: integer overflow in `COUNT` parameter
- https://github.com/redis/redis/pull/15073 `CLIENT TRACKING`: self-overlap returning non-zero loop index
- https://github.com/redis/redis/pull/15059 Use-after-free
- https://github.com/redis/redis/pull/15037 `XINFO STREAM`: wrong value in the per-slot memory tracking
- https://github.com/redis/redis/pull/15034, https://github.com/redis/redis/pull/15081 Issues processing corrupt RDB data
- https://github.com/redis/redis/pull/15021 `HEXPIRE`: overflow on fields count
- https://github.com/redis/redis/pull/14942 Fix `COMMAND GETKEYS for PFMERGE` with no source keys
- https://github.com/redis/redis/pull/15188 `cluster-announce-ip` rejecting hostnames (regression)
- https://github.com/redis/redis/pull/14667, https://github.com/redis/redis/pull/14886 Potential TCP stalls/deadlocks
- RediSearch/RediSearch#9484 Shard crash during background index scan of JSON documents with vector fields on Active-Active (CRDT) databases (MOD-15542)
- RediSearch/RediSearch#9635 Severe latency spikes and shard unresponsiveness when `EXPIRE` or `EXPIREAT` operations run concurrently with queries on large indexes (MOD-14930)


